The paper proposes a new framework for sequence generation using Generative Adversarial Nets (GAN) and reinforcement learning (RL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the development of algorithms and models for machine learning. The paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks, such as text generation, which falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses Monte Carlo search, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) and reinforcement learning (RL), making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also experiments with image captioning, which is a computer vision (CV) task, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of passing gradients from the discriminator to the generator, which is a common issue in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
